http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tamil-nadu/483-students-perform-dance-on-pots/article13990886.ece

A total of 483 students from Standard II to Plus-One of Cluny Matriculation Higher Secondary School performed a Bharatanatyam for six minutes on earthen pots to the tune of Bharathiar song ‘Bharata Samudayam Vazhgave’ here on Saturday.The event was organised as part of 55th school anniversary, and coming Pongal festival.They had practised for three months under the guidance of Latha Manickam, a dance teacher.Karthikeyan Jawahar, Indian Adjudicator for Elite World Records (UK) Private Limited, London; A.K. Senthil Kumar; and M.S. Irfan Ahamed, Indian Adjudicator for Asian Records Academy, Singapore; P. Jeganathan, Records Manager for India Records Academy, Mumbai; and L. Raj Krishna, Records Manager for Tamilan Book of Records, Chennai, were present.They said that the feat was a world record for highest number of women performing a dance event.They issued a certificate of record to Sister Anita, correspondent, and Sister Norah, principal. Individual certificates were given to all the participants.Organisers said that participants have been learning Bharatanatyam for many years now. Special training were provided to them for setting the world record.